# Lines starting with "#" will be ignored by Git.
# Write your commit message ABOVE these comments.

# type(scope): short description

# Example:
# feat(tasks): add recurring task support
#
# -------------------------------
# Commit Types
# -------------------------------
#
# feat:     new feature
# fix:      bug fix
# refactor: restructure code without changing behavior
# perf:     performance improvement
# style:    formatting only (whitespace, formatting)
# docs:     documentation changes
# test:     add or modify tests
# chore:    maintenance tasks (configs, dependencies)
# build:    build system changes
# ci:       CI/CD configuration changes
# revert:   revert a previous commit
# wip:      work in progress
# debug:    debugging changes
#
# -------------------------------
# Optional Body
# -------------------------------
#
# Explain WHY the change was made if needed.
#
# -------------------------------
# Optional Footer
# -------------------------------
#
# Closes #issue_number